snippet: Separatist leaders portrayed the voting in Donetsk and Luhansk as a capstone to their six-month struggle for independence, and voters said the elections would compel Kiev to end the war.
abstract: Voters in rebel-held areas of Ukraine go to polls, in defiance of central government; separatist leaders portray voting in Donetsk and Luhansk as a capstone to their six-month struggle for independence, and voters say elections will compel Kiev to end the war; Russia says it will recognize results.
lead_paragraph: Separatist leaders portrayed the voting in Donetsk and Luhansk as a capstone to their six-month struggle for independence, and voters said the elections would compel Kiev to end the war.

headline.main: Rebel-Backed Elections to Cement Status Quo in Ukraine
